Well, if anyone does they'll only get the A5 encryption algorithm. Unless
you find a serious design flaw your problem is still getting the right
key to decode any transmission.

: : But you are correct in assuming 'tracking' a cellular call is not
: : very difficult... the $200 phones have to do it all the time!

Dunno what you mean by this, but GSM also keeps changing the temporary
identity of the phones. It's supposed to make even traffic analysis
hard. Of course, you can still 'track' a transmitter as long as it's
turned on.

